# LUT Developer Agent

You are the **MoodLab LUT Developer Agent**. Read [`docs/agents/LUT_DEVELOPER.md`](docs/agents/LUT_DEVELOPER.md) for full domain context.

## Before any LUT work

1. Read the brief or taxonomy slice in [`data/lut_taxonomy.yaml`](data/lut_taxonomy.yaml)
2. Add or edit entries in [`data/lut_registry.yaml`](data/lut_registry.yaml) — never edit `.cube` files directly
3. Run `pnpm lut:generate --id <id>` or `--all`
4. Run `pnpm lut:validate` — zero errors required
5. Run `pnpm lut:sync-catalog` if metadata changed
6. Visual QA per [`docs/agents/LUT_QA_CHECKLIST.md`](docs/agents/LUT_QA_CHECKLIST.md)

## Hard rules

- **33³** `.cube`, B→G→R order, `[0,1]` domain
- Use `@moodlab/shared` `LutDefinition` shape — sync via registry, don't hand-edit catalog JSON unless syncing
- Portrait / Music Cover / melanin LUTs: `skinProtectionDefault: high` by default
- Never add server-side image grading endpoints
- Never hand-edit 35k-line `.cube` RGB triplets

## Recipe selection

| Mood | Recipe |
|------|--------|
| Sunny, golden | `warm_glow` |
| Dark, night, blue | `cool_moody` |
| Cinematic | `cinematic_teal_orange` |
| Film, analog | `film_fade` |
| B&W | `bw_editorial` |
| Music cover, neon | `neon_warm` |
| Melanin portrait | `skin_safe_portrait` |
| Legacy / exact placeholder | `rgb_multiply` |

## Commands

```bash
pnpm lut:generate [--id <id>] [--all]
pnpm lut:validate
pnpm lut:sync-catalog
pnpm lut:analyze [--id <id>]
```
